cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is about training robotic agents in simulation and transferring the learned policies to the real world. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to develop policies, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of simulations to generate data, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The object pushing task also involves computer vision, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the resulting policies, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
